ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 10, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ule1665702755478.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ule1665702755478.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ule1665702755478.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ule1665702755478\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ule1665702755478__uniface_datastore_418718\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.datastore</span> API provides access to the local browser-based database used for client-side data storage.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ule1665702755478__topic_d90082e1_d90083e1_d90084e1_d90085e1_d90086e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d356218e52\">\n                       \n Functions\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ule1665702755478__table_d15233e1_d15234e1_d15235e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Datastore Functions</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ule1665702755478__table_d15233e1_d15234e1_d15235e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Function</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ule1665702755478__table_d15233e1_d15234e1_d15235e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Description</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ule1665702755478__table_d15233e1_d15234e1_d15235e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ely1665702755621.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ely1665702755621.html\" title=\"Creates or updates the specified document in storage.\">put()</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ule1665702755478__table_d15233e1_d15234e1_d15235e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Creates or updates a JSON document in a client-side database.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ule1665702755478__table_d15233e1_d15234e1_d15235e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mmc1665702755696.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mmc1665702755696.html\" title=\"Retrieves a specified document from storage.\">get()</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ule1665702755478__table_d15233e1_d15234e1_d15235e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Retrieves the specified JSON object from a client-side database.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ule1665702755478__table_d15233e1_d15234e1_d15235e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mtf1665702755765.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mtf1665702755765.html\" title=\"Deletes the specified document from storage.\">remove()</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ule1665702755478__table_d15233e1_d15234e1_d15235e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Deletes the specified JSON document from a client-side database.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ule1665702755478__topic_d90087e1_d90088e1_d90089e1_d90090e1_d90091e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d356218e158\">\n                       \n                       Promises and Errors\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ule1665702755478__p_d127457e1_d127458e1_d127459e1\">All of these functions return a JavaScript Promise, such as the specified JSON document or a response. If the Promise cannot be fulfilled, an error or exception is returned. The most common errors are:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ule1665702755478__li_d46253e1_d46254e1_d46255e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">409 conflict</code> errors are returned when the database is unable to commit an action such as a <span class=\"keyword apiname\">put()</span> or <span class=\"keyword apiname\">remove()</span>, for example, a JSON document already exists with a specified <code class=\"ph codeph\">_id</code>, or when a specified <code class=\"ph codeph\">_rev</code> value does not match.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ule1665702755478__li_d46256e1_d46257e1_d46258e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">404 not found</code> exceptions, which are returned when an attempt is made\n               to retrieve data that does not exist. Such an exception might look like this:\n               <div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104ule1665702755478_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"ule1665702755478__codeblock_fpp_rpb_dwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">{\n status: 404,\n name: \"not_found\",\n message: \"missing\",\n error: true,\n reason: \"missing\",\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ule1665702755478__p_d127460e1_d127461e1_d127462e1\">You should always provide error handling for errors and exceptions. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104ule1665702755478_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"ule1665702755478__codeblock_qvk_spb_dwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">var myDoc = {\n _id: 'someid',\n _rev: '1-somerev'\n};\nuniface.datastore.put(myDoc).then(function () {\n // success\n}).catch(function (err) {\n if (err.name === 'conflict') {\n // conflict!\n } else {\n // some other error\n }\n});</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/etq1665702755550.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Client-Side Data Storage</a><p>Uniface dynamic server pages support client-side storage of data in a browser-based database, which makes it possible to save data locally when there is no connection to the server. This can be useful when you want to display read-only information that has previously been downloaded, or to save modified data until it can be synchronized or uploaded to the server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yqo1665702756208.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Promises</a><p>A promise is a placeholder for the return value of an operation that has been called asynchronously. It enables you to specify subsequent actions to be performed with that value when it is eventually received.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532733\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532733\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uniface.datastore Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 10, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The uniface.datastore API provides access to the local browser-based database used for client-side data storage. Functions Table 1. Datastore Functions Function Description put() Creates or updates a JSON document in a client-side database. get() Retrieves the specified JSON object from a client-side database. remove() Deletes the specified JSON document from a client-side database. Promises and Errors All of these functions return a JavaScript Promise, such as the specified JSON document or a response. If the Promise cannot be fulfilled, an error or exception is returned. The most common errors are: 409 conflict errors are returned when the database is unable to commit an action such as a put() or remove() , for example, a JSON document already exists with a specified _id , or when a specified _rev value does not match. 404 not found exceptions, which are returned when an attempt is made to retrieve data that does not exist. Such an exception might look like this: Explain this code { status: 404, name: \"not_found\", message: \"missing\", error: true, reason: \"missing\", } Copy You should always provide error handling for errors and exceptions. For example: Explain this code var myDoc = { _id: 'someid', _rev: '1-somerev' }; uniface.datastore.put(myDoc).then(function () { // success }).catch(function (err) { if (err.name === 'conflict') { // conflict! } else { // some other error } }); Copy Related Links Client-Side Data Storage Uniface dynamic server pages support client-side storage of data in a browser-based database, which makes it possible to save data locally when there is no connection to the server. This can be useful when you want to display read-only information that has previously been downloaded, or to save modified data until it can be synchronized or uploaded to the server. Promises A promise is a placeholder for the return value of an operation that has been called asynchronously. It enables you to specify subsequent actions to be performed with that value when it is eventually received. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}